{
  "page": "Ysabel Staunton",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\"><img alt=\"House Staunton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/50px-House_Staunton.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/75px-House_Staunton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/100px-House_Staunton.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Ysabel Staunton</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\"><img alt=\"House Staunton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/50px-House_Staunton.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/75px-House_Staunton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/100px-House_Staunton.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\">House Staunton</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/103_AC\" title=\"103 AC\">103</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)<i></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Ysabel Staunton</b> was a member of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\">House Staunton</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ysabel_Staunton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden%27s_Day_Ball\" title=\"Maiden&#39;s Day Ball\">Maiden's Day Ball</a> was held at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> to find a second wife and new queen for King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>. Many <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden\" title=\"Maiden\">maidens</a> across <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> came to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> in hopes of marrying the young king. Lyra was one of the many maidens who suffered what was called the \"<a href=\"/index.php/Maiden%27s_Day_curse\" title=\"Maiden&#39;s Day curse\">Maiden's Day curse</a>\" by being injured or scandalized after the ball was announced. In Ysabel's case, her supposed fondness for <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a> was gossiped about. It is possible that this was a rumor fabricated by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Unwin_Peake\" title=\"Unwin Peake\">Unwin Peake</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, who wished to promote his <a href=\"/index.php/Myrielle_Peake\" title=\"Myrielle Peake\">own daughter</a> as Aegon III's second queen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ysabel_Staunton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It is unknown how Ysabel Staunton is related to her contemporary relatives <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton\" title=\"Lord Staunton\">Lord Staunton</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Staunton\" title=\"Lady Staunton\">Lady Staunton</a>, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Staunton\" title=\"Joffrey Staunton\">Joffrey Staunton</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ysabel_Staunton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued3)#Ysabel_Staunton\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued3)\">Ysabel Staunton</a> calculation.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404012901\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.073 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.282 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 542/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10513/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5561/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 840/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1417/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.190/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.57 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  271.799      1 -total\n 96.31%  261.763      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 95.55%  259.694      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.94%   32.459     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  3.87%   10.520      3 Template:Infobox_label\n  2.26%    6.150      2 Template:Date\n  2.00%    5.426      2 Template:Ref\n  1.34%    3.645      2 Template:Ref/core\n  0.62%    1.695      1 Template:References\n  0.32%    0.858      1 Template:M